{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"75424e0b-c2d7-4584-9792-deb69e55f308","content":"The directory doesn't exist yet. No worries — here's what you need to configure in your `.csproj` to publish as a **dotnet tool** on NuGet.org:\n\n### Required `.csproj` properties\n\n```xml\n<PropertyGroup>\n  <OutputType>Exe</OutputType>\n  <TargetFramework>net8.0</TargetFramework>\n\n  <!-- Makes this a dotnet tool -->\n  <PackAsTool>true</PackAsTool>\n  <ToolCommandName>my-mcp-server</ToolCommandName>\n\n  <!-- NuGet metadata -->\n  <PackageId>MyMcpServer</PackageId>\n  <Version>1.0.0</Version>\n  <Authors>YourName</Authors>\n  <Description>An MCP server using stdio transport.</Description>\n  <PackageReadmeFile>README.md</PackageReadmeFile>\n  <PackageLicenseExpression>MIT</PackageLicenseExpression>\n</PropertyGroup>\n```\n\n### Key points\n\n| Property | Purpose |\n|---|---|\n| `PackAsTool` | Marks the project as a .NET tool |\n| `ToolCommandName` | The CLI command users invoke (e.g. `my-mcp-server`) |\n| `OutputType` must be `Exe` | Tools must be console apps |\n\n### Publish steps\n\n```bash\n# 1. Pack\ndotnet pack -c Release\n\n# 2. Push to NuGet.org\ndotnet nuget push bin/Release/MyMcpServer.1.0.0.nupkg \\\n  --api-key YOUR_API_KEY --source https://api.nuget.org/v3/index.json\n```\n\n### Users install with\n\n```bash\ndotnet tool install --global MyMcpServer\nmy-mcp-server   # runs via stdio\n```\n\nWould you like me to create the project or update an existing `.csproj`?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"94a28b14-2bbe-41d6-b7e4-d9d2549343d3","outputTokens":471,"requestId":"B02D:2779BD:D2463B:EF3800:6A027DC8"},"id":"6eab6a8c-bf83-40c4-80e6-780afe468769","timestamp":"2026-05-12T01:09:36.891Z","parentId":"8f258110-823e-4505-8d9b-0604bad982dd"}
